PART II — SCRAPED DATA OWNERSHIP & RESPONSIBILITY
=============================================================================

5. NO OWNERSHIP OF SCRAPED CONTENT

   Neither the authors of this Software, its contributors, its users,
   nor any organization employing or contracting with the above, acquire
   any ownership, copyright, license, or intellectual property rights
   over Scraped Content by the mere act of scraping, collecting,
   downloading, caching, indexing, transforming, or storing it.

   To be unambiguously clear:

     a) Scraping content does NOT transfer ownership of that content.
     b) Scraping content does NOT create a new copyright over that content.
     c) Scraping content does NOT grant a license to use, reproduce,
        distribute, display, or create derivative works from that content.
     d) Aggregating, reformatting, cleaning, deduplicating, or otherwise
        processing Scraped Content does NOT create new intellectual
        property rights over the underlying content.
     e) Storing Scraped Content in a database, dataset, file, or any
        other format does NOT constitute authorship of that content.
     f) Making Scraped Content available through an API, website, or
        service does NOT transfer or create rights.

6. ORIGINAL RIGHTS PRESERVED

   ALL rights in Scraped Content — including but not limited to copyright,
   trademark, trade secret, database rights, moral rights, publicity
   rights, privacy rights, and any other intellectual property or
   proprietary rights — belong to, and remain exclusively with, the
   Original Creators, authors, publishers, and/or rights holders.

   This applies without limitation to all types of content:

     - Text, articles, blog posts, comments, reviews, descriptions
     - Images, photographs, illustrations, graphics, icons, logos
     - Audio recordings, music, podcasts, sound effects
     - Video, animations, livestream recordings
     - Source code, compiled code, scripts, configuration files
     - Databases, datasets, spreadsheets, structured data
     - Trademarks, brand elements, trade dress, service marks
     - Personal data, biographical information, contact details
     - Metadata, tags, categories, taxonomies

7. AI AND MACHINE LEARNING

   The following additional terms apply to the use of Scraped Content
   in connection with artificial intelligence and machine learning:

     a) Training AI or ML models on Scraped Content does NOT grant
        ownership of the training data to the model creator, trainer,
        deployer, or any downstream user.

     b) AI/ML models trained on Scraped Content do NOT inherit any
        rights to the content used for training.

     c) Outputs generated by AI/ML models trained on Scraped Content
        may be subject to the intellectual property rights of Original
        Creators if the outputs are substantially similar to, derived
        from, or reproduce the training data.

     d) Users who train AI/ML models on Scraped Content are solely
        responsible for ensuring they have the legal right to use the
        content for training purposes, including compliance with
        applicable AI/ML regulations and opt-out mechanisms.

     e) The Software itself may include AI/ML capabilities (such as
        NuExtract integration). The license terms for the Software
        (Part I) apply to the Software's AI components. The data
        ownership terms (Part II) apply to any content processed
        by those components.

8. USER RESPONSIBILITY

   Users of this Software are solely and exclusively responsible for:

     a) Ensuring they have the legal right to scrape, store, process,
        analyze, transform, and/or redistribute any content they collect.

     b) Complying with all applicable laws, regulations, and legal
        frameworks, including but not limited to:
        - Copyright and intellectual property laws
        - The Computer Fraud and Abuse Act (CFAA) and equivalents
        - The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)
        - The California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA/CPRA)
        - The Digital Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA)
        - The EU Database Directive
        - The AI Act (EU) and other AI-specific regulations
        - Applicable terms of service of scraped websites
        - National and regional data protection laws

     c) Respecting robots.txt directives and other machine-readable
        access controls where technically feasible and legally required.

     d) Properly attributing and citing original sources when using or
        publishing Scraped Content.

     e) Honoring takedown requests, opt-out signals, and removal
        requests from rights holders in a timely manner.

     f) Implementing appropriate data retention and deletion policies
        for Scraped Content, particularly content containing personal
        data or sensitive information.

     g) Conducting data protection impact assessments where required
        by applicable law before scraping personal data at scale.

     h) Not using the Software to circumvent technical protection
        measures, access controls, or authentication mechanisms in
        violation of applicable law.

9. COMMUNITY DATASET

   The community dataset hosted at:
     https://huggingface.co/datasets/ray0rf1re/Site.scraped

   is community-contributed and subject to the following terms:

     a) The dataset maintainer (ray0rf1re / minerofthesoal) does NOT
        own, claim ownership of, or hold any rights to contributed content.

     b) All rights in contributed content remain exclusively with the
        Original Creators and rights holders.

     c) Contributors are solely responsible for ensuring they have the
        legal right to upload and share the content they contribute.

     d) Rights holders may request removal of their content via the
        GitHub issue tracker at:
        https://github.com/minerofthesoal/Scraper/issues

     e) Removal requests will be honored within a reasonable timeframe,
        not to exceed 30 days from receipt of a valid request.

     f) The dataset is provided for research and educational purposes.
        Commercial use of individual records may require separate
        permission from Original Creators.

10. CITATIONS

    Auto-generated citations (MLA 9th edition, APA 7th edition, and
    other formats) are provided as a convenience to assist users with
    proper attribution. However:

      a) Citations are generated algorithmically and may contain errors,
         omissions, or inaccuracies.

      b) Citations MUST be verified by the user before use in academic
         work, publications, legal proceedings, or any context where
         accuracy is required.

      c) Providing a citation does NOT constitute legal permission to
         use the cited content. Users must independently verify their
         right to use any cited material.

      d) Citation generation is a feature of the Software, not a legal
         service. No attorney-client relationship is created.

