    d) Major version changes (e.g., v2.x to v3.0) may introduce
       significant changes to rights and obligations. Users should
       review major version updates carefully.

    e) Minor version changes (e.g., v2.0 to v2.1) are intended to
       clarify, expand, or improve existing terms without fundamentally
       changing the license's intent.

16. GOVERNING INTERPRETATION

    Where this license is silent on a matter:

      a) For software-related matters, interpret in the spirit of the
         MIT License — permissive, with minimal restrictions.

      b) For data-related matters, interpret in the spirit of "nobody
         owns scraped data by scraping it" — Original Creators retain
         all rights.

      c) For AI/ML-related matters, interpret in the spirit of
         protecting Original Creator rights while permitting legitimate
         research and development.

